4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO NAVIGABLE
5 RIVERS AND STREAMS; REQUIRING UNIFORMITY AND LABELING OF DIGITAL MAPPING; PROVIDING
6 RESTRICTIONS ON SHOOTING AND HUNTING ON RIVERS AND ISLANDS; REQUIRING THE STATE
7 LIBRARY TO UPDATE AND MARK ITS GLOBAL INFORMATION SYSTEM MAP; AMENDING SECTIONS 23-
8 2-302 AND 90-1-404, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Digital mapping -- requirements. All persons and entities maintaining
13 digital maps of the state for electronic distribution shall update their maps in accordance with the digital map
14 maintained by the state library by August 1, 2025, and then within 30 days of the annual state library update of
15 the map afterward. Digital maps for electronic distribution must denominate and graphically mark previous
16 historical locations no longer occupied by navigable rivers as: "Private land surface owned by adjacent
17 landowner. Permission required."
18
19 Section 2. Section 23-2-302, MCA, is amended to read:
20 "23-2-302. Recreational use permitted -- limitations -- exceptions. (1) Except as provided in
21 subsections (2) through (5) (8), all surface waters that are capable of recreational use may be so used by the
22 public without regard to the ownership of the land underlying the waters.
23 (2) The right of the public to make recreational use of surface waters does not include, without
24 permission or contractual arrangement with the landowner:
25 (a) the operation of all-terrain vehicles or other motorized vehicles not primarily designed for
26 operation upon the water;
27 (b) the recreational use of surface waters in a stock pond or other private impoundment fed by an
28 intermittently flowing natural watercourse;
